{
  "$schema": "https://json.schemastore.org/claude-code-settings.json",
  "hooks": {
    "PostToolUse": [
      {
        "matcher": "Bash",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "bash -c 'output=$(jq -r \"(.tool_response.stdout // \\\"\\\") + \\\" \\\" + (.tool_response.stderr // \\\"\\\")\" 2>/dev/null); if echo \"$output\" | grep -qE \"reportAny|reportExplicitAny\"; then printf \"{\\\"hookSpecificOutput\\\":{\\\"hookEventName\\\":\\\"PostToolUse\\\",\\\"additionalContext\\\":\\\"STOP — AGENTS.md type-checking rule triggered. A reportAny/reportExplicitAny diagnostic means fix the underlying type, NOT add # pyright: ignore. Fix order: (1) TypedDict/dataclass/Protocol, (2) typed stub class, (3) typing.Self, (4) cast(T,...) at a single boundary. Only use # pyright: ignore as a LAST RESORT with a one-line comment explaining why the type cannot be tightened. Do NOT silence a diagnostic just to make the commit hook pass.\\\"}}\"; fi'"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
